AWS EC2 Api
An AWS EC2 Api is a programmatic interface provided by AWS that allows you to control and manage EC2 instances using
code instead of the web console.
Using three ways AWS API we can use:
1.AWS CLI
2.AWS API(For eg Python)
3.AWS CFT(Cloud Formation Template)
4.Terraform(It is an opens ourcxe tool used for Infrastructure as a Code)- It lets you manage cloud infrastructure 
using configuration file instead of manual setup)
5.AWS CDK
Terraform is generally preffered when you are using hybrid cloud model.
